channel.title: Returning Player
channel.description: I just started playing again today, and I wanted to know a good skill to train to make money, but also fairly inexpensive to work up. I had started fishing swordies when I started playing again a few months ago. I kind of want to do that, but I'm not sure if fishing will yield the most profit in the least amount of time.

item.title: Returning Player
item.dc:creator: @_Rich Rich
item.description:
@_Rich wrote:

[quote=“tonypker13, post:5, topic:246346”]Hunter.
Level 63-99.
Start trapping Chinchompas. You need 50-70k chins to get 99, and here are the prices. (You keep there stackable bodies.)
Chin price is the G.E.:
667gp.

667x60,000 = 40,020,000 GP.[/quote]

I got 99 hunter on my old account back when hunter wasn’t exactly popular, before the implings were released. I did them from 80-99 and I had to catch 44k or so total, 2k per day, I hunted for 2-4 hours a day, and took me about 2-3 weeks. Although I never had to share a spot or go looking for a world as there was usually never anyone hunting.

It’s still good cash I guess, but rather annoying finding and maintaining a spot.

item.title: Returning Player
item.dc:creator: @Tico135 Tico
item.description:
@Tico135 wrote:

If you are really really looking into getting back into the game I suggest buying a membership, at least for a month or two. From here, complete the quest swan song and fish monkfish. These are extremely quick for money and exp. These are much better than swordies and I guarantee you will notice a difference once you try. The hardest part of this is completing the quests in order to do swan song.
